To play the Minigames, you need Stamina for each action done. The Stamina Cost is varied depends on what type of Minigame you’re playing.
The Stamina automatically regenerates overtime when you’re staying on the Gathering map, and much more faster when you’re not playing the Gathering Mode. Stamina won’t regenerate during Minigames.
You can also spend LE to replenish Stamina, but the LE cost is increased with each consecutive purchase.
To pass a Minigame, you can either use the Key found in that game, or spend Stamina to skip the game entirely.
The main goal of the Gathering Mode is to gather as many materials as possible by playing the Minigames.
However, the amount of items you can carry is limited by the size of your Travel Bag. Items of the same type may be stacked in the same slot.

After a Gathering trips end (either by completing the final node, or you choose to go back to the Main Menu prematurely), all of the items that’re currently in your Travel Bag will be automatically transferred into your main Inventory.
You can access the Gathering Map from the Main Menu.
Each time you start a Gathering trip, a map with new route is generated by the system. A route is formed by 12 event nodes with different functions.
You can only process to the next node by completing the previous one. A Gathering trip only completes when you finishes the final node.
Most of the event nodes are categorized into different Minigames: Fishing, Foraging and Mining.
When you choose to exit the Gathering Map and return to the Main Menu, the next time you play Gathering Mode, a new route will be generated and your previous process will be reset.
Congratulations! You've got... nothing. Better luck next time (or not?)!
